Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddXMLAnalysis
    This class allows to add an analysis to the program by parsing an XML document containing the laboratory results from a sample of waste water discharges.
    Analysis
    This superclass keeps track of the basic information that an analysis of waste water dischargess must have: The name of the industry that discharged the waste water to a receiving body. The name of the laboratory that took the sample of water and performed the tests to determine the concentration of each pollutant. A 4 character number which serves the laboratory to identify the sample of waste water that was analyzed The date when the sample of waste water was obtained.
    App
    Description: The following class runs the COMPLIANCE APPLICATION FOR THE MONITORING AND CONTROL OF WASTE WATER DISCHARGES TO RECEIVING BODIES OF WATER.
    ComplianceResults
    This class contains the methods to verify that the laboratory results comply with the maximum levels allowed of heavy metals in a body of water.
    FinalResultsTextWriter
    This class prints the final results of a waste water sample in a text file after it has been validated with the compliance test.
    FinalResultsXMLWriter
    The new document will contain information of the observed concentrations of heavy metals pollution obtained at the laboratory.
    LabResults
    This class extends Analysis and keeps record of test results performed by the laboratory.
